Changes from upstream:
  - Translated the agent runtime target from the OpenAI Codex CLI to the
    Claude Code CLI.
  - Renamed AGENTS.md to CLAUDE.md (verbatim content with Codex-specific
    references swapped to their Claude Code equivalents).
  - Moved .agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md to .claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md
    and dropped the Codex-specific agents/openai.yaml manifests.
  - Converted .codex/agents/subgoal-prover.toml to
    .claude/agents/subgoal-prover.md (Claude Code subagent format).
  - Replaced .codex/config.toml MCP server registrations with .mcp.json
    files at each agent's project root.
  - Rewrote agents/verification/api/server.py and
    agents/generation/tests/run_example.sh to invoke `claude -p` instead
    of `codex exec`, with environment variables CLAUDE_BIN, CLAUDE_MODEL,
    CLAUDE_EFFORT, CLAUDE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS in place of their CODEX_ counterparts.
  - Updated skill text that referenced "Codex built-in web search" to
    reference Claude Code's built-in WebSearch tool, and updated the
    recursive-proving skill to use Claude Code's Agent tool with
    subagent_type=subgoal-prover in place of Codex's spawn_agent /
    wait_agent primitives.

The MCP servers, the verification JSON schema, the FastAPI surface, the
memory channel layout, and the mathematical procedures inside every
SKILL.md file remain byte-identical to upstream where not noted above.
